                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_256-item1">
                     <author key="person_f3587">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Sa'di</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_328">Bustan.</title>
                     <note>Inside front cover: a) Armorial bookplate of Gordon of Buthlaw. b) Printed slip, describing the MS, perhaps from a sale catalogue. The colophon states that the owner was Shaikh I'tibari,son of (reading walad for walid) the late Shaikh Muhammad Ja'far resident in ?, parganah ? Headings in red.</note>
                     <incipit>Bi-nam-i jahandar-i janafarin</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>As for Codrington/Reade No 251.</bibl>
                        <bibl>General Gordon's bequest of books and Turkish, Perian and Arabic manuscripts is mentioned, without details in the donations register under November 6 1841. The bequest is mentioned in J.R.A.S., vii, 1843, Annual Report, p. x, and the manuscripts are briefly listed in the Proceedings, pp. xxx-xxxi.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
